  <cateringDescription><![CDATA[<p>A continental breakfast is served in the bright and airy breakfast room looking out onto the gardens and lake. When it's warm you can have your breakfast on the lakeside terrace. If you choose half board you'll eat at <a data-udi="umb://document/95333cb49a2b4f6a9e152a22a297f9e5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/95333cb49a2b4f6a9e152a22a297f9e5}" title="Hotel Olivi Spa &amp; Natural Wellness"><span>Hotel Olivi Spa &amp; Natural Wellness</span></a>, located just 300 metres away. You can enjoy a choice of four courses with traditional Italian cuisine on the menu.</p>]]></cateringDescription>
  <cateringShortDescription></cateringShortDescription>
  <deactivateThisPage>0</deactivateThisPage>
  <description><![CDATA[<p>Hotel Eden's right in the centre of <a data-udi="umb://document/93a0ea3cd0334ca088eaf788bad0faba" href="/{localLink:umb://document/93a0ea3cd0334ca088eaf788bad0faba}" title="Sirmione">Sirmione</a> and on the lakefront next to the harbour. From here, the views of <a data-udi="umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473" href="/{localLink:umb://document/ae52b40037474a3eadb1c0692c464473}" title="Lake Garda">Lake Garda</a> are fantastic, plus it’s nice and easy to get to the ferry port and explore further afield.</p>
<p>The Eden's a family run hotel with excellent service. There’s a rich history here and, in the past, many famous faces have stayed here, including the poet Ezra Pound. The interiors have been completely modernised and the rooms feel very fresh with bright colours and wooden floors. The lakefront terrace has to be the best feature – head here and grab a drink while you enjoy the views. There’s a sun terrace too with loungers and direct lake access if you want to have a swim. If you’d rather use a pool then you’re welcome to use the facilities at the Eden’s sister hotel, <a data-udi="umb://document/95333cb49a2b4f6a9e152a22a297f9e5" href="/{localLink:umb://document/95333cb49a2b4f6a9e152a22a297f9e5}" title="Hotel Olivi Thermae &amp; Natural Spa">Hotel Olivi</a> located 300 metres away.</p>
<p>As you’re right in the centre of Sirmione there plenty of restaurants to head to for dinner. Try a different one each night. You can check with the hotel staff for their recommendations. If you choose half board, you'll eat dinner at Hotel Olivi where you'll get four courses each night with tasty local dishes.</p>
<p>Transfer time: approx. 45 mins by coach from Verona airport.</p>]]></description>
